libwav
------------------------------------------
libwave is a simple and tiny C library for reading or writing PCM wave (.wav)
files.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.0.6-1
  libwav-devel-0.1.0+git20180927-1bl1
  libwav0-0.1.0+git20180927-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.33.0-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  ninja-1.9.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/brglng/libwav

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/brglng/libwav.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libwav-0.1.0+git20180927-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libwav-0.1.0+git20180927-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libwav-0.1.0+git20180927-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libwav-0.1.0+git20180927-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libwav0-0.1.0+git20180927-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libwav-devel-0.1.0+git20180927-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libwav)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libwav.README
  /usr/share/doc/libwav/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/libwav/README.md

(libwav0)
  /usr/bin/cygwav-0.dll

(libwav-devel)
  /usr/include/wav/wav.h
  /usr/include/wav/wav_defs.h
  /usr/lib/libwav.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libwav.pc

